<paragraph blockId="45.[264,1323,1793,1899]" lastBlockId="46.[264,1325,284,1110]" lastPageId="46" lastPageNumber="47" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">
<emphasis box="[312,485,1793,1818]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Male genitalia</emphasis>
: Pygophore rather rectangular, with a small anterior apodeme, caudal margin truncate, produced into spinelike process ventrally, dorsal margin with a long spine like pigmented process at the point of articulation with tenth segment, a few stout, long setae in caudal 
<number box="[448,499,284,310]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" value="0.33">0.33</number>
and marginal shorter setae. Subgenital plate triangular, with a lateral submarginal row of long setae and marginal hairlike setae, especially those at caudal end long. Style, pigmented, with a slender long, apophysis with transverse rugae, preapical lobe well­developed. Connective Y­shaped, pigmented, stem longer than arm. Paraphyses convergent, in ventral view, twisted at apical 
<number box="[794,848,444,470]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" value="0.25">0.25</number>
, articulated proximally with both aedeagus and connective. Aedeagus tubular, dorsal apodeme well­developed, shaft slightly narrowed distally and apex curved anteriorly, gonopore apical.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="46.[264,1325,284,1110]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">
<emphasis box="[312,512,564,589]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Female genitalia</emphasis>
: 
<collectingCountry box="[529,588,564,590]" name="India" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Hind</collectingCountry>
margin of seventh sternum broadly produced medially with a median notch.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="46.[264,1325,284,1110]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">
